        "title": "fix(slack): wake interaction system events (rebased #56766)",
        "body": "Rebased port of #56766 onto current main.\n\n**Problem:** Slack block actions and modal lifecycle handlers enqueue system events but never request a heartbeat for the routed session — so interaction events can sit idle until an unrelated wake happens.\n\n**Fix:** Slack interaction handlers now request an `exec-event` heartbeat after a system event is successfully queued. Tests extended to assert wake behavior.\n\nOriginal author: @xinyuan0801\nCloses #28047",
